OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FAsylum hotel closures may  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fshift cost to councils     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Asylum seekers moved out of            
OL,6, government-funded hotels may be put    
OL,7, back into the same hotels with costs   
OL,8, "shunted" to local taxpayers because of
OL,9, councils' legal obligations,           
OL,10, councillors warn.                      
OL,12,FThe government plans to end contracts  
OL,13,Fwith 50 hotels housing asylum seekers  
OL,14,Fby the end of the year.                
OL,16,FOfficial figures show hiring these     
OL,17,Fhotels cost the taxpayer #8m a day.    
OL,19,FThe Local Government Association (LGA) 
OL,20,Fsay this cost may pass to councils, who
OL,21,Fare required to house refugees in need.
